msgid "Zero trackers"
msgstr ""

#: lib/lynxplanningpoker_web/controllers/page_html/privacy.html.heex:80
#, elixir-autogen, elixir-format
msgid "We count unique daily visitors: visiting the site multiple times in a day counts as one, and coming back tomorrow counts as one more. Instead of a cookie, each visit is fingerprinted in memory with a one-way SHA-256 hash of your IP, your User-Agent, the date and a server secret — and only that hash and a 2-letter country code (supplied by Cloudflare, the CDN in front of the site) are stored. Because the date is part of the hash input, the same person produces a different hash every day, so visits cannot be linked across days. The IP and User-Agent themselves are never written to the database."
msgstr ""

#: lib/lynxplanningpoker_web/controllers/page_html/privacy.html.heex:31
#, elixir-autogen, elixir-format
msgid "We keep a simple, anonymous count of unique daily visitors — no cookies, no identifiers, no third-party analytics service."
msgstr ""

#: lib/lynxplanningpoker_web/controllers/page_html/privacy.html.heex:53
#, elixir-autogen, elixir-format
msgid "Your IP is used in-memory for three things: to apply rate limits, to talk to Cloudflare Turnstile (anti-bot verification when creating a room), and — together with your User-Agent header, the date and a server secret — to produce a one-way hash that lets us count unique daily visitors without identifying you. None of these inputs are written to the database; only the hash is stored. When written to operational logs, the IP is truncated (the last octet for IPv4, the last 80 bits for IPv6) so that the original address cannot be reconstructed."
msgstr ""

